Decomposers are pure content → `SubstrateChange` streams with ZERO inline SQL
(protected property). The pipeline spine (IngestBatchPipeline working-set →
ConsensusAccumulatingWriter → NpgsqlWorkingSetApply) does all batching/dedup/Glicko
fold/COPY. The spec is the SEQUENCE (Rule #8) — right algorithm at the wrong stage is a
violation. Never change a SourceId. Do not create a new source by copying the nearest
neighbor. [Updated 2026-07-20: the seven historical lanes are collapsed — every
`*Decomposer.cs` now inherits the `Decomposer<T>` family and the architecture gate's
escape-hatch allowlists are empty sets (`DecomposerArchitectureGateTests.cs:30-35,148-172`);
dispatch is table-driven (`IngestDispatchTable.cs`). GH #406 closed on that evidence.
`.scratchpad/13` is historical, not a lane index.] Full rules:
`.github/instructions/decomposers.instructions.md` — read it.
